The paper deals with the design and analysis of online algorithms for routing virtual circuits, which involves network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves network routing and optimization, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of primal-dual approach suggests the involvement of optimization and information theory, which are covered by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with online algorithms, which can be considered as a subfield of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
